  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Radiographer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Duties & Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>⁠Perform diagnostic imaging procedures such as X-rays, CT scans and MRIs.</p></li><li><p>Position patients correctly to obtain the most accurate images and assist in the immobilization of patients if necessary.</p></li><li><p>⁠Operate and maintain imaging equipment, ensuring proper functioning and safety.</p></li><li><p>Follow established protocols for image production and patient identification.</p></li><li><p>Evaluate the quality of images to ensure diagnostic standards are met.</p></li><li><p>⁠Collaborate with radiologists and other healthcare professionals to discuss patient symptoms and imaging requirements.</p></li><li><p>Maintain patient records and update information as required. ⁠</p></li><li><p>Adhere to radiation safety guidelines and protocols to minimize radiation exposure to patients and staff.</p></li><li><p>⁠Provide patient education about procedures and address any concerns or questions.</p></li><li><p>⁠Assist in training and supervising student radiographers or other staff members.</p></li></ul><p>​</p><p><strong>Education & Experience</strong></p><ul><li><p>Proven experience as a Radiographer in a clinical setting.</p></li><li><p>⁠Strong knowledge of radiographic procedures and equipment.⁠</p></li><li><p>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</p></li><li><p>Ability to work effectively in a team as well as independently.</p></li><li><p>⁠Attention to detail and commitment to quality patient care.</p></li><li><p>⁠Proficient in using radiology information systems and electronic medical records.</p></li><li><p>Understanding of patient confidentiality and privacy regulations.</p></li><li><p>Must be a registered practitioner with Allied Health Professional Council.</p></li><li><p>Candidate with the experience of Ultrasound, Mammography, Angiography, will be an advantage.</p></li></ul><p><br /></p>",
